ShipTown

Postman collection OpenAPI spec

Introduction

API documentation for ShipTown

Base URL: https://demo.myshiptown.com

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

Authenticating requests

To authenticate requests, include an Authorization header with the value "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}".

All authenticated endpoints are marked with a requires authentication badge in the documentation below.

You can retrieve your token by visiting Menu > Setting > API > Create API Token.

API

GET api/activities

GET
https://demo.myshiptown.com
/api/activities
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/activities';
$response = $client->get(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request GET \
    --get "https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/activities" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/activities"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/activities'
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('GET', url, headers=headers)
response.json()

POST api/activities

POST
https://demo.myshiptown.com
/api/activities
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

log_name
string

Must not be greater than 255 characters.

Example:
bhhusiszbqpigms
description
string
required
Example:
Facere autem distinctio qui ut molestias placeat possimus.
properties
object
subject_type
string
Must be one of:
  • order
Example:
order
subject_id
integer

This field is required when subject_type is present.

Example:
7
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/activities';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'log_name' => 'bhhusiszbqpigms',
            'description' => 'Facere autem distinctio qui ut molestias placeat possimus.',
            'subject_type' => 'order',
            'subject_id' => 7,
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/activities" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"log_name\": \"bhhusiszbqpigms\",
    \"description\": \"Facere autem distinctio qui ut molestias placeat possimus.\",
    \"subject_type\": \"order\",
    \"subject_id\": 7
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/activities"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "log_name": "bhhusiszbqpigms",
    "description": "Facere autem distinctio qui ut molestias placeat possimus.",
    "subject_type": "order",
    "subject_id": 7
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/activities'
payload = {
    "log_name": "bhhusiszbqpigms",
    "description": "Facere autem distinctio qui ut molestias placeat possimus.",
    "subject_type": "order",
    "subject_id": 7
}
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()

POST

/api/admin/users
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

name
string
required

Must not be greater than 255 characters.

Example:
fwibxe
email
string
required

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters.

Example:
ysipes@example.org
role_id
string
required
Example:
quia
warehouse_id
string
warehouse_code
string
default_dashboard_uri
string

Must not be greater than 255 characters.

Example:
qrxvmnaqeeldzuik
Example request:

    [
        'headers' => [

            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'name' => 'fwibxe',
            'email' => 'ysipes@example.org',
            'role_id' => 'quia',
            'default_dashboard_uri' => 'qrxvmnaqeeldzuik',

https://demo.myshiptown.com
/api/configurations
requires authentication

Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:

business_name
string

Must not be greater than 200 characters.

Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/configurations';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'business_name' => 'fugo',
        ],
    ]
);

curl --request POST \
    "https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/configurations" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"business_name\": \"fugo\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/configurations"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "business_name": "fugo"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

POST
https://demo.myshiptown.com
/api/inventory-movements
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

warehouse_id
integer
required
Example:
9
product_id
integer
required
Example:
18
quantity
number
required

Must not be one of 0.

Example:

description
string
required

Must not be greater than 50 characters.

Example:
Repellendus quasi aut minus a debitis iure.
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();

    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'warehouse_id' => 9,
            'product_id' => 18,
            'quantity' => 278360.9323,
            'description' => 'Repellendus quasi aut minus a debitis iure.',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    "https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/inventory-movements" \

    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"warehouse_id\": 9,
    \"product_id\": 18,
    \"quantity\": 278360.9323,
    \"description\": \"Repellendus quasi aut minus a debitis iure.\"
}"

PUT api/mail-templates/{id}

PUT
PATCH
https://demo.myshiptown.com
/api/mail-templates/{id}
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

URL Parameters

id
integer
required

The ID of the mail template.

Example:
1

Body Parameters

subject
string
required

Must not be greater than 300 characters.

Example:
nsdgzgzqseqfpentgddevgqp
html_template
string
required
Example:
perferendis
text_template
string
Example:
consectetur
reply_to
string

Must be a valid email address.

Example:
ndickens@example.com
to
string[]

Must be a valid email address.

Example:
["brionna46@example.net"]
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/mail-templates/1';
$response = $client->put(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'subject' => 'nsdgzgzqseqfpentgddevgqp',
            'html_template' => 'perferendis',
            'text_template' => 'consectetur',
            'reply_to' => 'ndickens@example.com',
            'to' => [
                'brionna46@example.net',
            ],
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request PUT \
    "https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/mail-templates/1" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"subject\": \"nsdgzgzqseqfpentgddevgqp\",
    \"html_template\": \"perferendis\",
    \"text_template\": \"consectetur\",
    \"reply_to\": \"ndickens@example.com\",
    \"to\": [
        \"brionna46@example.net\"
    ]
}"

/api/modules/rms_api/connections
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Example:

Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

location_id
string

This field is required when id is null.

url
string

This field is required when id is null. Must be a valid URL.

Example:
http://www.ryan.com/
username
string

This field is required when id is null.

password
string

This field is required when id is null.

warehouse_code
string

Must not be greater than 5 characters.

Example:
jft

POST
https://demo.myshiptown.com
/api/modules/slack/config
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

incoming_webhook_url
string

Must be a valid URL.

Example:
http://schamberger.com/iure-error-rerum-quia-ea-totam-vel
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/modules/slack/config';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'incoming_webhook_url' => 'http://schamberger.com/iure-error-rerum-quia-ea-totam-vel',
        ],
    ]
);

    "https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/modules/slack/config" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"incoming_webhook_url\": \"http:\\/\\/schamberger.com\\/iure-error-rerum-quia-ea-totam-vel\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/modules/slack/config"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "incoming_webhook_url": "http:\/\/schamberger.com\/iure-error-rerum-quia-ea-totam-vel"
};

    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

requires authentication

Headers

string

POST
https://demo.myshiptown.com
/api/picklist/picks
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

quantity_picked
number

This field is required when quantity_skipped_picking is not present.

Example:
9877.97122
quantity_skipped_picking
number

This field is required when quantity_picked is not present.

Example:
1036870.6
order_product_ids
number[]
Example:
[3162517.84487]
Example request:

    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'quantity_picked' => 9877.97122,
            'quantity_skipped_picking' => 1036870.6,
            'order_product_ids' => [
                3162517.84487,
            ],
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    "https://demo.myshiptown.com/api/picklist/picks" \

    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"quantity_picked\": 9877.97122,
    \"quantity_skipped_picking\": 1036870.6,
    \"order_product_ids\": [
        3162517.84487
    ]
}"
